gate: OPEN
v:4 role:dev x:frontend
task: S88 T0 — Audit iOS auth friction paths
requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
sprint: S88

context: |
  Before changing behavior, document every code path that ends with the user
  typing username/password on the login screen. Reproduce on a physical iPhone
  with biometry enabled (client scenario: older device, Bulgarian locale).

steps:
  1. Trace cold start: useSessionBiometryLock → requestBiometricUnlock →
     loadBiometricCredentials → reloginWithBiometricCredentials.
  2. Trace resume: visibilitychange handler in useSessionBiometryLock.
  3. Trace failure: onBiometryFailed in useMobileShell → performUserLogout →
     blockBiometryUntilManualLogin in useAuthStore.logout.
  4. Trace JWT expiry: hydrateFromStoredSessionToken + isJwtExpired.
  5. Record whether user sees one or two system biometry prompts per open.
  6. Write findings to intel/S88_AUTH_FRICTION_AUDIT.md (paths, repro, severity).

out:
  - intel/S88_AUTH_FRICTION_AUDIT.md

done:
  - Audit doc lists all password-forcing paths with file:line refs.
  - Client repro steps documented (old iPhone, biometry on).
  - Recommended fix order aligns with T1–T3 tasks in this sprint.
